{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How quickly can I schedule Craftsman Pro wide-deck lawn mower repair service?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"&lt;p&gt;You can easily schedule a wide-deck lawn mower repair appointment online or by calling &lt;strong&gt;1-800-4-MY-HOME&lt;/strong&gt;. Sears Home Services offers flexible scheduling options, and in many areas, same-day or next-day appointments may be available depending on technician availability.&lt;/p&gt;"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What should I do if my Craftsman Pro wide deck lawn mower is vibrating excessively?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"&lt;p&gt;Excessive vibration in your Craftsman Pro wide deck lawn mower could be caused by several issues. First, check for debris caught inside the mower deck or pulley, as this can cause vibration. It could also be due to an unbalanced blade, in which case rebalancing the blades might help.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the issue persists, inspect the belt, pulley, and mandrel for damage. Additionally, loose bolts or nuts on the mower deck could cause vibration, so tightening them might resolve the problem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If these solutions don’t work, there may be an issue with the blade drive system. Schedule wide-deck mower repair to have a Sears Home Services technician correct the problem.&lt;/p&gt;"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why is my Craftsman Pro wide deck lawn mower not cutting grass evenly?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"&lt;p&gt;Uneven cutting by your mower can be caused by a few different factors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First, check the tire inflation on your mower; uneven tire pressure can lead to uneven cuts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that the mower deck is leveled correctly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you notice alternating stripes of taller and shorter grass, it may be due to mowing too quickly—try slowing down.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Worn or dull blades can also cause uneven cuts, so consider sharpening or replacing the blades for a cleaner cut.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If these tips don’t help you resolve the uneven cutting problem, have your Craftsman Pro wide-deck lawn mower serviced by a Sears Home Services technician.&lt;/p&gt;"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I repair my Craftsman Pro wide deck lawn mower myself?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"&lt;p&gt;Some Craftsman Pro wide deck lawn mower issues can be addressed by completing basic do-it-yourself repairs. Check the owner&apos;s manual to find common maintenance procedures and part replacements that you can do on your own.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For major repairs beyond your DIY capabilities, Sears Home Services offers professional repair services by trained technicians for a quick and reliable solution.&lt;/p&gt;"}}]}
